}{\#}8242;/b{\&}{\#}963; divided by the logarithm$\backslash$nof the velocity jump, where {\&}{\#}956;{\&}{\#}8242; is the effective elastic$\backslash$nshear modulus. For this prediction to be consistent with observed$\backslash$npropagation speeds of slow slip events in subduction zones appears$\backslash$nto require effective normal stresses as low as 1 MPa.},
